<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB9C833FE0BF807FDBC2495" box="[452,519,1922,1948]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13654" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13654" name="Muséum d'Histoire Naturelle de Grenoble" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="Herbarium">GRM</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDBE937FFB9C835FF72F823FE7723D4" blockId="3.[136,1452,1130,2093]" lastBlockId="5.[136,1451,158,221]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="206" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB9C833FF72F823FE0824C9" bold="true" box="[189,435,1958,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Taxonomic remarks</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB9C833FE19F822FD6024C9" box="[470,731,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balearicum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB9C833FE19F822FD6024C9" box="[470,731,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Hieracium balearicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been confused with 
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB9C833FBC2F822FB0724C9" box="[1037,1212,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB9C833FBC2F822FB0324C9" box="[1037,1208,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elisaeanum">H. elisaeanum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In our opinion, the typification of these two names gives an adequate interpretation to consider 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB9C833FBCBF84EFB1124ED" box="[1028,1194,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balearicum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB9C833FBCBF84EFB1124ED" box="[1028,1194,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">H. balearicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a separate species, based on several vegetative and reproductive characters (Sáez 
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB9C833FC96F86AFC362B01" box="[857,909,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">et al</emphasis>
., unpublished, in prep.): the basal leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB9C833FA5FF86AFEB32B25" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elisaeanum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB9C833FA5FF86AFEB32B25" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">H. elisaeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have shorter petioles, the leaves are usually less hairy on adaxial surface and the phyllaries have a different indumentum density: stellate hairs are rare or even absent (vs. dense in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FC52FF1AFB8523B1" box="[925,1086,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balearicum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFBFC835FC52FF1AFB8523B1" box="[925,1086,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">H. balearicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and glandular hairs are rare (vs. numerous in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFBFC835FED5FF46FE0723D5" box="[282,444,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balearicum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFBFC835FED5FF46FE0723D5" box="[282,444,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">H. balearicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
